goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the most common bird species involved in bird strikes and prioritize measures to mitigate their impact.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by time of day?

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the time of day when bird strikes are most likely to occur and take preventive measures accordingly.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by aircraft type?
goals.visualization: Pie chart of bird strikes by aircraft type
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand which aircraft types are most vulnerable to bird strikes and take appropriate measures to reduce their risk.

goals.question: What is the cost of damage caused by bird strikes?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of cost of damage by year
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the financial impact of bird strikes and prioritize measures to reduce their cost.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_csv('birdstrikes.csv')

# Convert date field to datetime type
data['Incident Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Incident Date'], format='%m/%d/%Y', errors='coerce')

# Drop rows with NaT values
data = data[pd.notna(data['Incident Date'])]

# Extract year from date field
data['Year'] = data['Incident Date'].dt.year

# Group by year and count number of incidents
yearly_counts = data.groupby('Year')['Record ID'].count().reset_index()

# Plot line chart
sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Record ID', data=yearly_counts)

# Set chart title
plt.title('What is the frequency of bird strikes per year?', wrap=True)

# Add horizontal line for average number of incidents per year
avg_incidents = yearly_counts['Record ID'].mean()
plt.axhline(avg_incidents, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average ({avg_incidents:.2f})')

# Add legend
plt.legend()

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_csv('birdstrikes.csv')

# Which bird species is responsible for the most strikes?
species_counts = data['Species Name'].value_counts().reset_index()
species_counts.columns = ['Species Name', 'Count']

# Plot bar chart
sns.set_style('whitegrid')
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.barplot(x='Species Name', y='Count', data=species_counts.head(10), palette='Blues_d')
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.xlabel('Bird Species')
plt.ylabel('Strike Count')
plt.title('Which bird species is responsible for the most strikes?')

# Add max value line
max_count = species_counts['Count'].max()
plt.axhline(max_count, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Count: {max_count:.2f}')
plt.legend()

plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_csv('birdstrikes.csv')

# Convert Time of Day to datetime format
data['Time of Day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Time of Day'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
data = data[pd.notna(data['Time of Day'])]
data['Time of Day'] = data['Time of Day'].dt.strftime('%H:%M')

# Create stacked bar chart
sns.set_style("whitegrid")
sns.set_palette("husl")
ax = sns.countplot(x="Time of Day", hue="Flight Phase", data=data, order=data['Time of Day'].value_counts().index)
ax.set(xlabel='Time of Day', ylabel='Number of Bird Strikes')
ax.set_title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by time of day?')

# Add legend
handles, labels = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()
ax.legend(handles=handles, labels=labels)

# Rotate x-axis labels for legibility
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_csv('birdstrikes.csv')

# Convert date fields to date types
data['Incident Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Incident Date'], format='%m/%d/%Y', errors='coerce')

# Drop rows with NaT values
data = data[pd.notna(data['Incident Date'])]

# Extract year from date
data['Year'] = data['Incident Date'].dt.year

# Aggregate cost of damage by year
cost_by_year = data.groupby('Year')['Cost'].sum().reset_index()

# Create bar chart of cost of damage by year
sns.set_style('whitegrid')
sns.barplot(x='Year', y='Cost', data=cost_by_year, color='blue')
plt.title('What is the cost of damage caused by bird strikes?')
plt.ylabel('Cost')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Add a line for the maximum cost
max_cost = cost_by_year['Cost'].max()
plt.axhline(y=max_cost, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Maximum cost: ${max_cost:,.2f}')

plt.legend()
plt.show()
```
